data-triple-N3.o: "The accordion (from German Akkordion, from Akkord - "musical chord, concord of sounds") is a box-shaped musical instrument of the bellows-driven free-reed aerophone family, sometimes colloquially referred to as a squeezebox. A person who plays the accordion is called an accordionist."@en
